Sep 25 2008	Not Bad Not Great	I stayed at the Quality Hotel September 20-22.The best part about this hotel is the location; you're right in the heart of downtown Montreal, only a few blocks' walk from a variety of shops, restaurants, bars and night clubs.The downsides? Some of the rooms are very outdated (friends of ours had better luck in other rooms). For example, our room had a very old TV that had the alarm clock built-in! The mini-bar is $10 per day, and our fridge was really old. The bedding also left a little to be desired - very firm mattress, average sheets/pillows, and a comforter that had the color and texture of a burlap sack.The front desk attendants also warned us to watch our luggage, bags, etc. everywhere we went in the hotel outside of our room. They said that unattended bags are always getting stolen, especially from the lobby. However, I'm sure this isn't unique to this particular hotel; it probably happens anywhere in downtown hotels.All in all, if you're looking for a decently-priced hotel with basic amenities but access to all that downtown Montreal has to offer, this is the hotel for you. If you want a hotel experience that's anything above ordinary, I suggest you look elsewhere.	
