Jun 3 2004	Good location good price.	My friends and I spent a few nights in this hotel and were pleasantly surprised. I guess we had low expectations but everything turned out great. The parking is in a secure garage and the food in the restaurant downstairs was great. We got a really good deal on the rooms from expedia so we weren't sure what to expect for the price. We were in walking distance to a lot of places and there's a grocery store right across the street. I'd probably stay there again if I ever go back to Montreal again. This is a perfect hotel if you plan on sightseeing Montreal and go places.	
Jun 2 2004	bang for the buck it has lots of value	Great location, just 1 block off of the center of St Catherine street. Close to the local subway which I found so easy to navigate. Private Garage asures safe parking. Great resturaunt called Mango's adjacent to the hotel located on the main floor. ( they serve a great breakfast) and keep a well stocked bar. The Front Desk was an excellent help, always happy to make dinner reservations for us and never being off when recamending a place to eat or visit. The rooms were clean &amp; quaint, the bathroom is a bit small but definetly sufficent, the tub was deep enough for me to soak my 6 foot 240 pound frame which is nice after a day off treking around the city. Right accross the street is a full service grocery store(great for the budget concious) or if you just need something you forgot to pack. Considering I paid less then $300 for a 4 night stay I would recamend this hotel and may even stay there again. It would have been nice to have a few more amenities (like a pool) but hey I was there to see the city not lounge around a hotel.	
Oct 20 2003	Cresent Street NIGHTLIFE!! NIGHTLIFE!!	The Quality Inn Downtown on Crescent Street 1 block south of St Catherines has been recently refurbished and is clean and safe. No it's not the Ritz but for $65-$90.00 USD depending on the season also consider the fact that within a 6 block radius of the Quality there is some of the best nightlife on this continent...!!!!!!!!!Restaurants, Cafes, Bars, Disco, Jazz, Rock, Irish, sophisticated to grunge, and when the bars close at 3 (If you have been there for a while they close the doors at 3 and let you stay till 4 usually drinking for free by now if you had been taking care of your bartender) now you only have a two short blocks to stumble home to your hotelWhen checking in ask for Jerry (one of the managers) introduce your self to him and he will take excellent care of you!! Larry	
